7 (3) “Community-based shelter” means a shelter that meets the
8 Department’s standards for the operation of shelters.
9 (4) “Department” means the Department for Children and Families.
10 (5) “Extreme weather event” means extreme hot or cold temperatures or
11 weather events, such as hurricanes, flooding, or blizzards, that create
12 hazardous conditions for outdoor habitation by humans.
13 (6) “Homeless” means lacking a fixed, regular, and adequate nighttime
14 residence.
