16 individual is legally responsible and who live and intend to stay in Vermont.
17 “Household” includes individuals who reside together as one economic unit,
18 including those who are married, parties to a civil union, or unmarried.
19 (8) “Unsheltered homelessness” means sleeping in a location not
20 designed for or ordinarily used as a regular sleeping accommodation.
